---
By: St. Maximus
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 102
    Verse: 3
Tags:
  - Desire
---
As a bird tied by the leg, when it starts to rise upwards, is pulled back
to earth by the string, so the mind which has not yet attained
desirelessness. ...is pulled back to the earth by desires.
